---
description: Require shared PHP files using require_once with __DIR__-based paths (no bare relative includes)
globs: **/*.php
alwaysApply: false
---

- **Shared infrastructure MUST be loaded using `require_once` + `__DIR__`**
  - Use `require_once` for shared files to prevent double-includes.
  - Use `__DIR__` so includes work from any current working directory.
  - **DO NOT** use bare relative paths like `require_once 'includes/connect.php';` in new/edited code.

- **Canonical shared includes**
  - **DB connection + DB helpers**: [V:\includes\connect.php](mdc:includes/connect.php)
  - **Page chrome**: [V:\includes\header.php](mdc:includes/header.php) and [V:\includes\footer.php](mdc:includes/footer.php)
  - **Version constant**: [V:\includes\version.php](mdc:includes/version.php)

- **Include patterns (root vs subdirectory)**

```php
// Root-level file (e.g., V:\index.php)
require_once __DIR__ . '/includes/connect.php';
require_once __DIR__ . '/includes/version.php';
include __DIR__ . '/includes/header.php';
// ...
include __DIR__ . '/includes/footer.php';
```

```php
// Subdirectory file (e.g., V:\admin\admin_panel.php)
require_once __DIR__ . '/../includes/connect.php';
require_once __DIR__ . '/../includes/version.php';
include __DIR__ . '/../includes/header.php';
// ...
include __DIR__ . '/../includes/footer.php';
```

- **Page-specific assets MUST be configured before including the header/footer**
  - See [V:\includes\header.php](mdc:includes/header.php) for `$extra_css` handling.
  - See [V:\includes\footer.php](mdc:includes/footer.php) for `$extra_js` handling (including `:defer` support).
